         <p>
<hi rend="bold">[438]</hi>
         </p>
         <p>
<hi rend="bold">Monday, June 24</hi><hi rend="bold superscript underline">th</hi><hi rend="bold">, 1912.</hi>
         </p>
         <p>I wrote a <ref xml:id="610">short letter</ref> to the 'Times' answering <ref xml:id="643" display="no">a long one</ref> from 
<persName xml:id="2639">D<hi rend="superscript underline">r</hi> Vernon Bartlet</persName>, who made an appeal to religious Anglicans to allow Welsh Disestablishment to pass!</p>
         <p>At 11 a.m. the Committee of Chapter met in my house.  We sate for two hours.  I then wrote out a Report, and sent it to the 
<persName xml:id="325">Dean</persName>.</p>
         <p>
<hi rend="bold underline">I shewed 
<persName xml:id="2640" display="no">young Lawrence</persName> &amp; 
<persName xml:id="2641" display="no">his wife</persName> over the Abbey</hi>.  We spent an hour &amp; a half in the Church.</p>
         <p>
<persName xml:id="112">Ella</persName> &amp; her guests went to the theatre.  I remained at home.  
<persName xml:id="1681">Cyril Hayward</persName> came to see me, &amp; stayed till nearly prayer&#8211;time.</p>
         <p>
<hi rend="bold">[439]</hi> 
